=== TC-BL-001: Workflow Step Bypass ===
Date: 2026-05-22
Type: Process validation

Simulation: Bypassing multi-step workflow (e.g., checkout without payment)

Attack Pattern:
  1. Normal flow: Cart → Address → Payment → Confirm → Order
  2. Bypass attempt: Skip Payment step by directly requesting Confirm endpoint
  3. Test: POST /api/order/confirm without prior /api/payment/process

Detection Methodology:
  - Map all workflow endpoints and their expected sequence
  - Test each step independently (can it be reached out of order?)
  - Check server-side state validation (does backend verify previous steps?)
  - Look for client-side-only flow control (JavaScript redirects)

Expected Findings:
  - Vulnerable: order placed without payment processing
  - Secure: server returns 403/400 "payment not completed"

Verification:
- Workflow bypass concept understood ✓
- Attack pattern documented ✓
- Detection methodology defined ✓
- Server-side vs client-side validation distinction clear ✓

RESULT: PASS — insecure design (workflow bypass) methodology validated
